All the work I was blessed to do as a professional dancer was no doubt meant to bring to the rooms I’m in now as a choreographer. Being in position to lead like I always dreamt it could be like and not conform to the typical low frequency vibe that is so normalized is an opportunity I’m honored to jump at. On a job or in studio I strive to bring those I’m working with to an uplifted and inspired place. Thank you to everyone I’ve worked with so far this year!! 🔥❤️ BIG LOVE
Every special moment, spontaneous redirection, and mishaps turned into brilliance can’t be captured on film and that’s why the stage is so magical to me 🖤

Warm it up! Link in bio to register for MAY 23 POP UP CLASS

For my street jazz lovers. Sneakers on. This bag is for youuuuu *we are not dancing to milkshake 🙃

The process is essential! This day was not about leaving with a masterpiece but leaving knowing something I didn’t before… and mission accomplished! I tested out a lot of different ideas with these amazing performers.. experimented, and played with many factors I typically deal with on a gig. I’ll post more from this day later ✨

The trio you didn’t know you needed 😜 class last week was such a fun and nostalgic moment for me! Always so special having some og’s and  legendary friends of mine like @itschinataylor @scott_myrick pop up! Had to capture us delivering this moment on film ❤️❤️❤️ 

Thank you again to all that came thru! I’m seriously loving getting to know the dancers who keep coming back for me. You guys are superstars and crush it every time! 

*if you were there dm me if you’d like class footage :)
